Sec. 30001: The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau’s annual budget is cut from $12 billion to $6.5 billion, effective immediately, reducing its enforcement staff and regulatory reach by roughly half.

Sec. 30002: All unspent money previously allocated for the Green and Resilient Retrofit Program for Multifamily Housing is rescinded, eliminating up to hundreds of millions in planned energy-efficiency grants for low-income housing projects.

Sec. 30003: The Securities and Exchange Commission’s Reserve Fund is abolished; its remaining balances are transferred to the Treasury’s general fund on October 1, 2025, and the Fund itself is formally closed, ending the SEC’s independent whistleblower award authority.

Sec. 30004: An additional $1 billion is appropriated, available until September 30, 2027, for domestic manufacturing and supply-chain initiatives under the Defense Production Act, specifically to boost critical mineral processing, semiconductor fabrication, and munitions production. [end of text]


